	<Language_en_US>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILDING_WATERSHRINE">
			<Text>Nato-oh Siskoom</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILDING_WATERSHRINE_HELP">
			<Text>Requires no maintenance and is available earlier than the Shrine that it replaces. Building the Nato-oh Siskoom near to fresh water, especially river mouths, will give a burst of [ICON_PEACE] Faith.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CIV5_BUILDINGS_WATERSHRINE_TEXT">
			<Text>Traditionally, the Blackfoot believed that they were allied to a race of underwater spirit-people known as the Suyitapis. The Suyitapis were seen as the power source for many sacred items. Because of this, the Blackfoot hold a traditional disdain or taboo for entering or taking from bodies of water.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILDING_WATERSHRINE_STRATEGY">
			<Text>In order to capitalize on the Nato-oh Siskoom's bonus faith, place cities near sources of fresh water -- especially Lakes and Oases.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILDING_BUFFALOPOUND">
			<Text>Buffalo Pound</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILDING_BUFFALOPOUND_HELP">
			<Text>Unlike the Water Mill it replaces, requires Plains instead of a River and gives +1 [ICON_FOOD] and +1 [ICON_PRODUCTION] Production to sources of [ICON_RES_BISON] Bison worked by the city. Reveals a nearby source of Bison.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CIV5_BUILDINGS_BUFFALOPOUND_TEXT">
			<Text>Buffalo Pounds were typically fenced off dugouts that the Blackfoot would chase buffalo into. Once the buffalo was within the pound, it would be easier to kill.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILDING_BUFFALOPOUND_STRATEGY">
			<Text>Make sure to build Camps on your new [ICON_RES_BISON] Bison resources.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_PROMOTION_COUNTSCOUP1">
			<Text>Counts Coup</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_PEDIA_PROMOTION_COUNTSCOUP1">
			<Text>Counting Coup</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_PROMOTION_COUNTSCOUP1_HELP">
			<Text>This unit gains a small amount of experience when it starts its turn adjacent to a non-barbarian enemy, or on a tile containing [ICON_RES_BISON] Bison.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CLBLACKFOOT_WATERSHRINE_NOTIFICATION">
			<Text>Our Elders believe that the Suyitapis inhabit local waters. This revelation has inspired {2_Faith}[ICON_PEACE] Faith in the people of {1_Place}.</Text>
		</Row>
